ion disappears. The whole\nsituation is later discussed with the help of Raychaudhury equation and the\nresults compared with previous cases. This work is the generalisation of our\nprevious article where we have taken $\\alpha =1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Oct 2017 16:04:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Dec 2017 17:58:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 6 Nov 2019 17:42:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-07"}
