 radio emission from GRB 170817A. We fit an\nafterglow off-axis jet model to the X-ray and radio data and find that the\nobservations are explained by a viewing angle $\\theta_{\\rm\nobs}\\approx16^\\circ-26^\\circ$, GRB jet energy $E\\sim10^{48.5}-10^{49.5}~{\\rm\nerg}$, and external density $n\\sim10^{-5}-10^{-1}~{\\rm cm}^{-3}$ for a\n$\\xi_e\\sim 0.1$ non-thermal electron acceleration efficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Oct 2017 17:54:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Nov 2017 18:56:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-05"}
