onized O VI accounts for\n$\\approx8\\%$ of the oxygen budget. As O VI traces an ion with expected\nequilibrium ion fractions of $\\lesssim 0.2$, the highly ionized CGM may\nrepresent a significant metal reservoir even for dwarfs not expected to\nmaintain gravitationally shock heated hot halos.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Oct 2017 18:00:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 10 Nov 2017 15:25:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Nov 2017 19:12:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-29"}
